      "description": "Open Application - Tech Artist at Tanglewood Games.\n\nTanglewood Games is an accredited Gold Service Unreal Engine Partner providing top-tier engineering and technical art services. Projects include Hogwarts Legacy, Steel Hunters, Harry Potter: Quidditch Champions, Grounded, Funko Fusion, F1 Manager series. Client studios include Warner Bros. Games and SEGA.\n\nWHAT YOU'LL NEED:\n- Proven background as Technical Artist on Unreal Engine projects\n- Deep knowledge of performance trace analysis (Unreal Insights)\n- Strong familiarity with materials and Niagara systems optimization\n- Background with various platforms and platform-specific tools\n- Strong capability with Editor Tools and Utility scripting\n- Familiarity with source control (Perforce)\n- Ability to diagnose and solve complex technical problems\n\nSALARY: Intermediate £48k | Senior £66k | Principal £77,650\n\nBENEFITS: Private Healthcare (Vitality), Dental/Optical cashplan, 25 days leave + festive closedown, Enhanced Maternity/Paternity, Personal wellbeing budget.\n\nINTERVIEW: Technical interview (60 min) + Final interview with directors.\n\nContact: David Chin (Recruiter) | jobs@tanglewoodgames.com\nLocation: Hartlepool Marina / Fully Remote | 40+ employees"
