      "description": "Junior Technical Artist - Larian Studios\nLocation: Barcelona (On-site) | Full-Time\nStudio: Larian Studios (Baldur's Gate 3, Divinity: Original Sin 2)\n\nWith multiple awards to our name, Larian Studios is looking for a Junior Technical Artist to join the team and help craft the high calibre games our fans have come to expect.\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES:\n- Provide technical follow-up to the art team in regards to performance and guidelines\n- Design, implement and optimize shaders while meeting artistic and technical requirements\n- Develop art pipeline tools and extensions with an eye towards usability and efficiency\n\nREQUIREMENTS:\n- Understanding of mathematics including trigonometry and linear algebra with ability to apply them effectively\n- 1-2 years of experience in game development or related fields\n- Basic concepts of 3D rendering (render stages, screen space operations, Physically Based Rendering)\n- Understanding of digital art content creation pipelines (high/low-poly modelling, unwrapping, baking, texturing, level building)\n- Proficiency in Python with understanding of code architecture to develop maintainable tools\n- Experience with Maya, Houdini, Substance Designer and Painter\n- Ability to work with technical documentation\n- Team oriented with strong desire for collaborative participation across different geographic locations\n\nNICE TO HAVES:\n- Knowledge of high level coding languages (C#, C++, etc.) and HLSL, both in real-time and DCC context\n\nWHAT THEY OFFER:\n- International team of 500+ employees across 7 studios worldwide\n- Open, collaborative environment where ideas are welcome\n- Experienced managerial team of top game developers\n- Inclusive environment with activities organized by studios and employees\n\nApply: https://jobs.lever.co/larian/4c9c09a6-7be1-4748-89f0-00f7ce26face"
