      "url": "https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4402394127/",
      "priority": "medium",
      "description": "Technical Art Generalist - NeoRonin Interactive\nLocation: Remote Europe | Full-Time\n\nWe are developing an operational and tactical RTS set in a stylized vision of modern warfare. Looking for a Technical Art Generalist who bridges art and technology, maintains visual quality across the pipeline.\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES\n\nArtistic Foundation:\n- Design, adjust, and review assets ensuring units, silhouettes, and environments read instantly in RTS context\n- Apply color theory, composition, lighting, and visual hierarchy to keep scenes cohesive and cinematic\n- Create animatics, 3D block-outs, and concept bashes to prototype visual ideas\n\nUnreal Engine 5:\n- Build scalable, performance-friendly master materials with deep understanding of UE5 material parameters, texture packing, and optimization\n- Handle lighting and rendering across indoor/outdoor environments (Lumen is a plus)\n- Create, implement, and optimize in-engine VFX in Niagara: explosions, ambient effects. Unity VFX Graph or Houdini-to-engine also welcome\n- Support UI effects in UMG: selection indicators, icon effects, menu transitions\n- Work within Unreal Blueprints to hook up art assets, trigger VFX, build simple procedural tools\n- Use UE5 profiling tools to identify bottlenecks and keep art within performance budgets\n\n3D Asset Production:\n- Contribute to or review hard surface assets: military vehicles, weaponry, architectural structures\n- Work within PBR workflows, non-destructive texturing, and efficient texture packing\n- Handle LOD creation and distance load optimization\n\nQuality and Collaboration:\n- Conduct technical and aesthetic reviews of internal and outsourced 3D assets\n- Provide clear actionable feedback; bridge art and engineering teams\n- Research emerging UE5 technologies to continuously improve the art pipeline\n\nREQUIREMENTS\n\nCore:\n- Shipped production experience in Technical Art or Art Generalist role in game development\n- Solid working knowledge of UE5: materials, shaders, lighting, performance profiling\n- Strong traditional art fundamentals: color theory, composition, lighting, visual hierarchy\n- VFX experience in modern real-time engine (Niagara preferred, Unity VFX Graph or Houdini-to-engine accepted)\n- Mastery of PBR workflows and non-destructive texturing in Substance Painter or equivalent\n- Comfortable reading and modifying Unreal Blueprints for art integration and simple tooling\n- Proficient in Blender or equivalent DCC, Substance 3D Painter, and Photoshop\n- Understanding of readability challenges in RTS, MOBA or turn-based games\n- Experienced working remotely and asynchronously\n- Fluent English\n\nStrong Plus:\n- Hard surface 3D modeling skills with clean topology and optimization\n- Experience with UI VFX and implementation in UMG\n- Knowledge of rigging, animation principles, and animation blueprint setup in UE5\n- Experience with asset customization systems in UE5\n- Familiarity with Houdini for procedural art and pipeline tooling\n- Proficiency with Substance 3D Designer\n- Experience with Perforce or Git in game production\n\nApply: Send portfolio and CV to recruitment@neoronin.co — Subject: \"Technical Art Generalist\"\nNote: Applications sent via LinkedIn may not be considered.",
      "contactTitle": "Head of Operations & Cofounder"
